  process: [
    {
      step: '01',
      title: 'Use-Case Definition and Feasibility',
      duration: 'Weeks 1 to 2',
      description: 'We work with you to define exactly what the model should do, what good output looks like, and where the hard boundaries are. We assess whether an LLM is the right tool at all, sometimes a rules engine or a simpler approach is cheaper and more reliable, and we agree the success criteria the evaluation harness will measure against.',
    },
    {
      step: '02',
      title: 'Model Selection and Data Residency Review',
      duration: 'Weeks 2 to 3',
      description: 'We select candidate models based on capability, cost, latency and residency requirements. Where the Privacy Act 1988 or internal policy applies, we determine whether a hosted API with zero-retention terms is acceptable or whether an open-weight model served in an Australian region is required, and we document that decision for your compliance team.',
    },
    {
      step: '03',
      title: 'Prompt Engineering and Tool Design',
